Loading Packages (Review)

Suppose we want to load the tidyverse and gapminder packages.

An incorrect approach:

  library(tidyverse)
  library(gapminder)

Another incorrect approach:

  library(pacman)
  p_load(tidyverse)
  p_load(gapminder)

The correct approach:

  library(pacman) 
  p_load(tidyverse, gapminder)

Grouping and Summarizing

summarize()

  gapminder %>%
    filter(year == 1997) %>%
    summarize(avgLifeExp = mean(lifeExp))
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   avgLifeExp
##        <dbl>
## 1       65.0
  gapminder %>%
    filter(year == 1997) %>%
    mutate(gdp = pop * gdpPercap) %>%
    summarize(totGDP = sum(gdp)/(10^9)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   totGDP
##    <dbl>
## 1 41006.
  gapminder %>%
    filter(year == 1997) %>%
    mutate(gdp = pop * gdpPercap) %>%
    summarize(avgLifeExp = mean(lifeExp),
              totGDP = sum(gdp)/(10^9)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 2
##   avgLifeExp totGDP
##        <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1       65.0 41006.

You can use the following functions inside of summarize():

  • mean()
  • sum()
  • median()
  • min()
  • max()

group_by()

  gapminder %>%
    filter(year == 1997) %>%
    group_by(continent) %>%
    mutate(gdp = pop * gdpPercap) %>%
    summarize(avgLifeExp = mean(lifeExp),
              totGDP = sum(gdp)/(10^9)) 
## # A tibble: 5 x 3
##   continent avgLifeExp totGDP
## * <fct>          <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 Africa          53.6  1561.
## 2 Americas        71.2 14567.
## 3 Asia            68.0 12791.
## 4 Europe          75.5 11508.
## 5 Oceania         78.2   579.
  gapminder %>%
    group_by(year) %>%
    mutate(gdp = pop * gdpPercap) %>%
    summarize(avgLifeExp = mean(lifeExp),
              totGDP = sum(gdp)/(10^9)) 
## # A tibble: 12 x 3
##     year avgLifeExp totGDP
##  * <int>      <dbl>  <dbl>
##  1  1952       49.1  7038.
##  2  1957       51.5  8896.
##  3  1962       53.6 11004.
##  4  1967       55.7 14248.
##  5  1972       57.6 18421.
##  6  1977       59.6 22318.
##  7  1982       61.5 25382.

## 10  1997       65.0 41006.
## 11  2002       65.7 47266.

Plotting using ggplot2

Text.

Scatter Plots

data_97_df <- gapminder %>%
            filter(year == 1997) 
ggplot(data_97_df, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp)) +
  geom_point()

ggplot(data_97_df, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) +
  geom_point()

ggplot(data_97_df, aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) +
  geom_point(size = 2.5)

ggplot(data_97_df, aes(x = gdpPercap/1000, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) +
  geom_point(size = 2.5) +
  ggtitle("Life Expectancy vs. Output") +
  labs(x = "GDP per capita (USD, 1000s)",
       y = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
       color = "Continent")

  ggplot(data_97_df, aes(x = gdpPercap/1000, y = lifeExp, color = continent)) +
    geom_point(size = 2.5) +
    ggtitle("Life Expectancy vs. Output") +
    labs(x = "GDP per capita (USD, 1000s)",
         y = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
         color = "Continent") +
    ylim(0,100) +
    xlim(0,50)

Line Plots

continent_allyears_df <- gapminder %>%
                      group_by(year, continent) %>%
                      summarize(avgGDPPercap = mean(gdpPercap))

continent_allyears_df
## # A tibble: 60 x 3
## # Groups:   year [12]
##     year continent avgGDPPercap
##    <int> <fct>            <dbl>
##  1  1952 Africa           1253.
##  2  1952 Americas         4079.
##  3  1952 Asia             5195.
##  4  1952 Europe           5661.
##  5  1952 Oceania         10298.
##  6  1957 Africa           1385.
##  7  1957 Americas         4616.
##  8  1957 Asia             5788.
##  9  1957 Europe           6963.
## 10  1957 Oceania         11599.
## # ... with 50 more rows
ggplot(continent_allyears_df, 
        aes(x = year, y = avgGDPPercap/1000, color = continent)) + 
    geom_line()

ggplot(continent_allyears_df, 
        aes(x = year, y = avgGDPPercap/1000, color = continent)) + 
    geom_line(size = 1) +
    ggtitle("Continent GDP per capita Over Time") +
    labs(x = "Year",
         y = "Average GDP per capita (USD, 1000s)",
         color = "Continent")

ggplot(continent_allyears_df, 
        aes(x = year, y = avgGDPPercap/1000, color = continent)) + 
    geom_line(size = 1) +
    ggtitle("Continent GDP per capita Over Time") +
    labs(x = "Year",
         y = "Average GDP per capita (USD, 1000s)",
         color = "Continent") +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0))

Histograms

data_57_97_df <- gapminder %>%
                  filter(year %in% c(1957,2007))

data_57_97_df
## # A tibble: 284 x 6
##    country     continent  year lifeExp      pop gdpPercap
##    <fct>       <fct>     <int>   <dbl>    <int>     <dbl>
##  1 Afghanistan Asia       1957    30.3  9240934      821.
##  2 Afghanistan Asia       2007    43.8 31889923      975.
##  3 Albania     Europe     1957    59.3  1476505     1942.
##  4 Albania     Europe     2007    76.4  3600523     5937.
##  5 Algeria     Africa     1957    45.7 10270856     3014.
##  6 Algeria     Africa     2007    72.3 33333216     6223.
##  7 Angola      Africa     1957    32.0  4561361     3828.
##  8 Angola      Africa     2007    42.7 12420476     4797.
##  9 Argentina   Americas   1957    64.4 19610538     6857.
## 10 Argentina   Americas   2007    75.3 40301927    12779.
## # ... with 274 more rows
ggplot(data_57_97_df, aes(lifeExp)) +
    geom_histogram()

ggplot(data_57_97_df, aes(lifeExp)) +
    geom_histogram() +
    ggtitle("Life Expectancy Frequency Plot") + 
    labs(x = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
         y = "Count")

ggplot(data_57_97_df, aes(lifeExp)) +
    geom_histogram(aes(fill = factor(year))) +
    ggtitle("Life Expectancy Frequency Plot") + 
    labs(x = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
         y = "Count", 
         fill = "Year")

ggplot(data_57_97_df, aes(lifeExp)) +
    geom_histogram(aes(fill = factor(year)), 
                    binwidth = 5) +
    ggtitle("Life Expectancy Frequency Plot") + 
    labs(x = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
         y = "Count", 
         fill = "Year")

ggplot(data_57_97_df, aes(lifeExp)) +
    geom_histogram(aes(fill = factor(year)), 
                    binwidth = 5,
                    position = "dodge") +
    ggtitle("Life Expectancy Frequency Plot") + 
    labs(x = "Life Expectancy (Years)",
         y = "Count", 
         fill = "Year")
